MAT|1|1||The book of the nativity of Jesus the Messiah, the son of David, son of Abraham.
MAT|1|2||Abraham begat Isaac: Isaac begat Jacob: Jacob begat Judah and his brothers:
MAT|1|3||Judah begat Pharez and Zara of Tamar: Pharez begat Hezron: Hezron begat Ram:
MAT|1|4||Ram begat Aminadab: Aminadab begat Nahshon: Nahshon begat Salmon:
MAT|1|5||Salmon begat Boaz of Rahab: Boaz begat Obed of Ruth: Obed begat Jesse:
MAT|1|6||Jesse begat David the king: David begat Solomon of the wife of Uriah:
MAT|1|7||Solomon begat Rehoboam: Rehoboam begat Abia: Abia begat Asa:
MAT|1|8||Asa begat Jehoshaphat: Jehoshaphat begat Joram: Joram begat Uzziah:
MAT|1|9||Uzziah begat Jotham: Jotham begat Ahaz: Ahaz begat Hezekiah:
MAT|1|10||Hezekiah begat Manasseh: Manasseh begat Amon: Amon begat Josiah:
MAT|1|11||Josiah begat Jeconiah and his brothers, in the captivity of Babylon.
MAT|1|12||And after the captivity of Babylon, Jeconiah begat Salathiel: Salathiel begat Zerubbabel:
MAT|1|13||Zerubbabel begat Abiud: Abiud begat Eliakim: Eliakim begat Azor:
MAT|1|14||Azor begat Zadok: Zadok begat Achim: Achim begat Eliud:
MAT|1|15||Eliud begat Eleazar: Eleazar begat Matthan: Matthan begat Jacob:
MAT|1|16||Jacob begat Joseph, the husband of Mary, of whom was born Jesus who is called the Messiah.
MAT|1|17||All the generations, therefore, are, from Abraham to David fourteen generations, and from David to the captivity of Babylon fourteen generations, and from the captivity of Babylon to the Messiah fourteen generations.
MAT|1|18||And the birth of Jesus the Messiah was thus. While his mother Mary was betrothed to Joseph, before they had cohabited, she was found to be with child by the Holy Spirit.
MAT|1|19||And Joseph her husband was a righteous man, and unwilling to expose her: and he thought of putting her away privately.
MAT|1|20||And while he contemplated these things, an angel of the Lord appeared to him in a dream, and said to him: Joseph, son of David, fear not to take Mary thy wife; for that which is conceived in her, is from the Holy Spirit:
MAT|1|21||and she will bear a son; and thou shalt call his name Jesus, for he will resuscitate his people from their sins.
MAT|1|22||Now all this that occurred, was to fulfill what was spoken of the Lord by the prophet:
MAT|1|23||Behold, a virgin will conceive, and will bear a son, and thou shalt call his name Emmanuel, which is interpreted, Our God with us.
MAT|1|24||And when Joseph rose from his sleep, he did as the angel of the Lord commanded him, and took his wife.
MAT|1|25||And he knew her not, until she had borne her firstborn son, and called is name Jesus.
MAT|2|1||Now when Jesus was born in Bethlehem of Judaea, in the days of Herod the king, there came Magi from the east unto Jerusalem,
MAT|2|2||saying: Where is the king of the Jews that is born? For we have seen his star in the east, and have come to worship him.
MAT|2|3||And Herod the king heard, and he was disturbed; and all Jerusalem with him.
MAT|2|4||And he assembled all the chiefs of the priests and the scribes of the people, and inquired of them, Where is the birthplace of the Messiah?
MAT|2|5||And they said: In Bethlehem of Judaea; for thus it is written in the prophet:
MAT|2|6||Thou also, Bethlehem of Judaea, art not the little among the kings of Judaea, for a king shall come from thee who shall rule my people Israel.
MAT|2|7||Then Herod privately called the Magi, and learned from them at what time the star appeared to them.
MAT|2|8||And he sent them to Bethlehem, and said to them, Go, search diligently for the child; and when ye have found him, come and tell me, that I also may go and worship him.
MAT|2|9||And they, when they had heard from the king, went forward: and lo, the star they had seen in the east went before them, until it came and stood over where the child was.
MAT|2|10||And when they saw the star, they rejoiced much, with great joy.
MAT|2|11||And they entered the house; and they saw the child, with Mary his mother; and they fell down and worshipped him: and they opened their treasures, and presented to him gifts, gold, and myrrh, and frankincense.
