MAT|6|12||And forgive us our debts, as we forgive our debtors:
MAT|6|13||And bring us not into temptation, but deliver us from evil: For thine is the kingdom, and the power, and the glory, for ever and ever: Amen.
MAT|6|14||For if ye forgive men their faults, your Father who is in heaven will also forgive you.
MAT|6|15||But if ye shall not forgive men, your Father also forgiveth not you your faults.
MAT|6|16||And when ye fast, be not sad like the hypocrites. For they distort their faces, that they may be seen of men to fast. Verily I say to you, they have gotten their reward.
MAT|6|17||But, when thou fastest, wash thou thy face, and anoint thy head:
MAT|6|18||that thou mayest not be seen by men as a faster, but by thy Father who is in secret: and thy Father who seeth in secret, will recompense thee.
MAT|6|19||Lay not up for yourselves treasures on the earth, where moth and rust spoil, and where thieves dig through and steal.
MAT|6|20||But lay up for yourselves treasures in heaven, where no moth and no rust can spoil, and no thieves dig through nor steal.
MAT|6|21||For where your treasure is, there will your heart also be.
MAT|6|22||The lamp of the body is the eye. If therefore thy eye shall be sound, thy whole body will be luminous.
