MAT|6|29||Yet I say to you, that not even Solomon in all his glory, was arrayed like one of them.
MAT|6|30||And if God so clothe the grass of the field, which exists to-day, and tomorrow falls into the oven, will he not much more [clothe] you, ye small in faith?
