JHN|19|38||After these things, Joseph of Ramath, for he was a disciple of Jesus, and kept concealed through fear of the Jews, requested of Pilate, that he might take away the body of Jesus. And Pilate permitted. And he came, and bore away the body of Jesus.
JHN|19|39||And there came also Nicodemus, he who previously came to Jesus by night, and he brought with him a compound of myrrh and aloes, about a hundred pounds.
