JHN|20|1||And the first day of the week, in the morning, while it was yet dark, Mary Magdalena came to the sepulchre: and she saw that the stone was removed from the grave.
JHN|20|2||And she ran, and came to Simon Cephas, and to that other disciple whom Jesus loved, and said to them: They have taken away our Lord from the sepulchre, and I know not where they have laid him.
JHN|20|3||And Simon set out, and the other disciple, and they were going to the sepulchre.
JHN|20|4||And they both ran together; but that disciple outran Simon, and came first to the sepulchre.
JHN|20|5||And he looked in, and saw the linen cloths lying: but he did not go in.
JHN|20|6||And after him came Simon; and he entered the sepulchre, and saw the linen cloths lying;
