ACT|13|24||And, before his advent, he sent John to proclaim the baptism of repentance to all the people of Israel.
ACT|13|25||And while John was fulfilling his ministry, he said: Who, suppose ye, that I am? I am not he. But lo, he cometh after me; of whom I am not worthy to untie his shoe-strings.
ACT|13|26||Men, brethren, children of the stock of Abraham, and all who, with you, fear God, to you is this word of life sent.
ACT|13|27||For, those inhabitants of Jerusalem and their chiefs, did not apprehend it; neither [did they apprehend] also the writings of the prophets, which are read every sabbath; but they condemned him, and fulfilled all the things written.
