ACT|13|45||And when the Jews saw the great assembly, they were filled with envy, and set themselves against the words which Paul spoke, and blasphemed.
ACT|13|46||And Paul and Barnabas said openly: To you first, ought the word of God to be spoken; but because ye repel it from you, and decide, against yourselves, that ye are not worthy of life eternal, lo, we turn ourselves to the Gentiles.
