ROM|3|17||and the path of peacefulness they have not known:
ROM|3|18||and the fear of God is not before their eyes.
ROM|3|19||Now we know, that whatever the law saith, it saith to them who are under the law; that every mouth may be stopped, and all the world be guilty before God.
ROM|3|20||Wherefore, by the deeds of the law, no flesh is justified before him: for, by the law, sin is known.
ROM|3|21||But now, the righteousness of God without the law, is manifested; and the law and the prophets testify of it:
ROM|3|22||even the righteousness of God, which is by faith in Jesus Messiah, for every one, and on every one, that believeth in him: for there is no distinction;
ROM|3|23||for they have all sinned, and failed of the glory of God.
ROM|3|24||And they are justified gratuitously, by grace, and by the redemption which is in Jesus Messiah;
ROM|3|25||whom God hath preconstituted a propitiation, by faith in his blood, because of our sins, which we before committed,
