ROM|3|27||Where then is glorying? It is annihilated. By what law? by that of works? Nay: but by the law of faith.
ROM|3|28||We therefore conclude, that it is by faith a man is justified, and not by the works of the law.
ROM|3|29||For, is he the God of the Jews only, and not of the Gentiles? Nay: of the Gentiles also.
ROM|3|30||Because there is, one God, who justifieth the circumcision by faith, and the uncircumcision by the same faith.
ROM|3|31||Do, we then nullify the law by faith? Far be it. On the contrary, we establish the law.
ROM|4|1||What then shall we say concerning Abraham the patriarch, that by the flesh he obtained?
